CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 18, 1970, pg. 29, reads: "Stargell Versus New Stadium - Willie Stargell, super slugger with the Pittsburgh Pirates, stand tall on the tartan turf of the new Three Rivers Stadium during a practice session.  Stargell is the only player in major league baseball that hit seven home runs over the right field roof at old Forbes Field."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball player Willie Stargell, on field at Three Rivers Stadium
